=== Aerodynamic Drag

The interaction os a spacecraft with the upper atmosphere can sap away energy from the orbit. Below 500km and even more significantly below 150km, drag acts to decrease the apogee of the orbit. The equation for drag is shown in *@3-drag*.

$
  a_"drag" = 1/2 rho(r) v^2 C_d A/m
$<3-drag>

Typically $C_d approx 2.2$ and the $A"/"m$ is assumed to be an average parameter. The air density $rho$ itself is a parameter based on several variables such as position, altitude, solar activity etc. One simplified model of the air density is shown in *@3-simple-air-density*.

$
  rho = rho_0 exp(-h/H) quad quad H = (k T)/(m g)
$<3-simple-air-density>

Where $H$ is the scale height. Another problem arises as $H(T)$ and $T(r)$. The temperature throughout the atmosphere varies as shown in *@3-temp-plot*.

#grid(
  columns: 2,
